WEBVTT

03:14.896 --> 03:16.596
3:52 p.m.

03:23.938 --> 03:25.672
I brought you somethin'.

03:28.575 --> 03:31.178
I only drink organic juices.

03:31.212 --> 03:34.681
Y'all need to get rid of your sugar
machine and enter the 21st century.

03:35.216 --> 03:37.752
Be sure to bring that up
at the next board meeting.

03:37.785 --> 03:39.053
Why am I in homicide?

03:39.086 --> 03:42.023
I checked your jacket.
You're a stick-up man, not a killer.

03:43.556 --> 03:45.993
And you pullin' all that rippin' and
runnin' out there in the streets.

03:46.861 --> 03:48.595
That's gonna make you
a lot of enemies.

03:48.628 --> 03:51.198
Make sense you feel
the need to be strapped,

03:51.232 --> 03:54.534
but that's gonna open you up to
a major conflict with the law.

03:58.571 --> 04:02.442
That gun they found in your
vehicle had shaved numbers.

04:03.543 --> 04:05.780
That's a mandatory nickel
in a federal joint.

04:06.847 --> 04:09.549
And with your priors,
maybe more.

04:09.582 --> 04:12.519
Depends on how the prosecutor
wanna push it.

04:22.263 --> 04:25.066
They're gonna run that nine
through IBIS.

04:26.767 --> 04:31.471
They're gonna test the ballistics
and check the striations.

04:32.006 --> 04:34.842
And if there's a body
attached to it,

04:36.043 --> 04:38.678
you're goin' away forever
and a day just like that song.

04:39.013 --> 04:42.984
"Forever and a Day. Yeah, man,
that... Heatwave, right?

04:43.683 --> 04:46.287
Man, my mother used to listen
to that on HUR.

04:47.687 --> 04:48.688
So did mine.

04:50.024 --> 04:52.760
Melvin Lindsey used to rock
that on the regular.

04:55.930 --> 04:56.964
Look, man.

04:59.300 --> 05:02.635
You in the murder house, 'cause I figured
we could do each other a couple solids.

05:02.669 --> 05:06.539
You help me put down
an outstandin' homicide or two

05:06.573 --> 05:11.578
and it's possible that that
problem of yours could go away.

05:11.946 --> 05:14.281
I don't know anything
about any murders.

05:14.315 --> 05:16.050
That ain't the world
I drive through.

05:19.053 --> 05:22.655
But something interesting comes
to mind that you might like.

05:23.057 --> 05:24.691
I'm listening.

05:28.329 --> 05:29.696
Turn it off.

05:30.998 --> 05:35.602
- Talk about it.
- Alright.

05:35.970 --> 05:40.908
Some big-time lawyer connected
through his work to the street,

05:40.941 --> 05:44.045
reached out to a man I've been
knowing since we were kids.

05:44.078 --> 05:46.747
My man gave the lawyer my name.

05:47.915 --> 05:52.853
- And?
- What, the lawyer? Some old white dude.

05:52.887 --> 05:55.322
He's got a young wife,
much younger than him.

05:55.356 --> 05:57.158
Heh, his round 2.

05:57.892 --> 06:00.327
Anyway, he's havin' a problem
with his woman.

06:00.361 --> 06:03.831
Kinda problem
he wants solved permanent.

06:04.732 --> 06:07.567
He tried to hire you
to kill his wife?

06:08.035 --> 06:09.804
And that's a bet.

06:09.837 --> 06:14.141
- How much?
- My man say 50,000.

06:15.843 --> 06:17.344
That right there is real money.

06:17.378 --> 06:20.714
Yeah, it is. But that ain't me.

06:21.382 --> 06:24.819
- You tell that to the lawyer?
- Oh, I never spoke to him.

06:24.852 --> 06:26.619
I held on to his number, though.

06:26.653 --> 06:27.922
Why?

06:27.955 --> 06:31.624
In case, I got into a situation
like I'm in today.

06:32.960 --> 06:34.328
You got a name for me?

06:34.361 --> 06:39.166
No, but the number's still in my
phone, the one that got confiscated

06:39.200 --> 06:42.602
when y'all illegally searched
my vehicle this afternoon,

06:43.003 --> 06:45.372
so you can use this though,
right?

06:45.406 --> 06:46.673
Not me.

06:47.908 --> 06:50.177
But, I mean, like, it's good
information like I'm free to go.

06:50.211 --> 06:53.781
Oh, oh, just don't...
Don't get ahead of yourself, Cray.

06:54.415 --> 06:57.017
You're not exactly
out of this situation just yet.

07:05.159 --> 07:06.894
What high school you go to?

07:07.828 --> 07:09.897
The only high school,
HD Woodson.

07:10.831 --> 07:15.402
The only high school.
I went to Cardozo, the Clerks.

07:16.203 --> 07:18.172
The Clerks. Oh, man.

07:19.874 --> 07:22.776
- You somethin'.
- Look, can I get that juice?

07:23.077 --> 07:26.413
Oh, yeah. Organic, right. I'm gonna
run out to Whole Foods right quick.

07:26.447 --> 07:28.681
You just stay right here.
Don't go anywhere.

07:33.454 --> 07:37.725
Back in school
I used to row from out there.

07:37.758 --> 07:39.093
Which one? This dock?

07:39.126 --> 07:41.162
Yeah, up at those red lights.

07:42.463 --> 07:45.698
- You in military?
- Yeah, I served in the Middle East.

07:46.133 --> 07:47.701
How did you get
into this line of work?

07:47.735 --> 07:49.370
I was a SOCOM, special ops.

07:49.403 --> 07:53.207
After that I worked for the Triple Canopy
outfit in Afghanistan personal security.

07:53.240 --> 07:55.442
So this was
a natural progression.

07:55.476 --> 07:57.278
I'm just doin'
what I was trained to do.

08:02.082 --> 08:03.683
So tell me what you need?

08:04.118 --> 08:08.822
My wife is, uh, considerably
younger than I am.

08:09.290 --> 08:14.195
She has been, uh, unfaithful

08:15.262 --> 08:16.931
since the day we met.

08:18.999 --> 08:21.235
I thought she'd change
but, uh,

08:22.836 --> 08:24.305
marrying her
was a mistake.

08:25.973 --> 08:28.008
- Terrible mistake.
- Get a divorce.

08:29.076 --> 08:30.778
Yeah.

08:31.212 --> 08:34.215
My first wife,
she damn near cleaned me out.

08:35.115 --> 08:37.117
Another settlement
would ruin me.

08:38.519 --> 08:41.855
Frankly,
I can't abide the betrayal.

08:43.857 --> 08:46.126
Or the loss of my self-esteem.

08:48.562 --> 08:49.863
I want her to pay.

08:51.899 --> 08:55.269
Say what you want. Exactly.

09:02.276 --> 09:03.310
I want you to kill her.

09:05.846 --> 09:07.781
But you haven't even
told me her name.

09:09.116 --> 09:12.886
- What?
- Her name. What's her name?

09:13.954 --> 09:14.989
It's Gina.

09:17.558 --> 09:19.026
Her name is Gina.

10:29.630 --> 10:34.168
Excuse me, I was wondering if you
knew anything about this book.

10:34.201 --> 10:37.037
If it's any good,
I mean it's for my father.

10:37.071 --> 10:41.608
Um, I'm not familiar with it.
You should ask the person who works here.

10:41.642 --> 10:43.010
Oh.

10:46.647 --> 10:48.115
What do you got there?

10:49.149 --> 10:53.854
It's "Appointment in Samarra"
by John O'Hara.

10:54.221 --> 10:56.023
Some say
he's better than Fitzgerald.

10:56.924 --> 10:58.092
Them's fightin' words.

10:59.293 --> 11:03.397
- Have you read O'Hara?
- No. No, not yet, I'd like to.

11:05.299 --> 11:09.103
It's about a self-destructive
man in a doomed marriage.

11:09.136 --> 11:12.239
Sounds real upbeat.
Me, I like happy endings.

11:15.008 --> 11:16.276
Nice talking with you.

11:17.277 --> 11:18.479
Hey, wait a second.

11:19.680 --> 11:23.884
I never do this, but would
you like to get a cup of coffee?

11:24.284 --> 11:25.486
Lunch or somethin'?

11:26.920 --> 11:30.090
- I can't, but thank you anyway.
- Just lunch. Conversation.

11:30.124 --> 11:31.458
Maybe I'll learn somethin'
about books

11:31.492 --> 11:34.928
and, you know,
the Appointment in the Sahara.

11:37.398 --> 11:41.268
I'm sure this isn't the first time
you've done something like this

11:41.301 --> 11:44.304
and you're very charming,
but I can't.

11:45.172 --> 11:48.475
- You want to though.
- You don't lack confidence.

11:49.309 --> 11:52.012
I'm married.
It would be wrong.

11:53.414 --> 11:55.048
I'll tell you what?

11:56.049 --> 11:58.452
I'm heading up the street
to the Hitching Post.

11:58.485 --> 12:01.488
It's a soul food spot
on second and Upshur.

12:02.189 --> 12:05.692
If you wanna meet me, fine.
I will be there.

12:05.727 --> 12:08.295
- Nice meeting you.
- Bob.

12:19.072 --> 12:20.441
Thank you, darling.

12:20.474 --> 12:23.043
You got it, baby,
I'll be right back to take your order.

13:37.251 --> 13:38.418
Gina!

13:39.620 --> 13:41.255
Gina.

14:20.294 --> 14:21.729
Gina, it's me.

14:21.763 --> 14:24.565
I know I'm supposed to call your
disposable, but you're not pickin' up.

14:25.365 --> 14:28.068
I've been trying to reach you
for days, please hit me back.

14:44.484 --> 14:48.355
- It's been a while.
- I've been busy.

14:48.388 --> 14:51.158
Hmm, too busy for your mentor?

14:51.191 --> 14:54.328
Don't be so sensitive.
I bought you your coffee.

14:54.361 --> 14:55.863
What?
You want a kiss, too?

14:55.897 --> 14:58.365
And a piece of chocolate
for my pillow.

15:01.703 --> 15:04.371
What happened to that tip I gave you?
You never said anythin'.

15:04.906 --> 15:06.106
Which one?

15:06.139 --> 15:09.877
- White dude wanted to off his wife.
- Oh, that... Pasadeno.

15:09.911 --> 15:12.880
No, he died before I had the
opportunity to meet with him.

15:12.914 --> 15:16.650
So you never got to give him that bullshit
story about you being special ops?

15:23.256 --> 15:24.391
What do you mean he died?

15:24.424 --> 15:26.226
You know,
like when you stop bein' alive.

15:26.259 --> 15:27.361
Funny.

15:28.930 --> 15:31.598
Leonard Sanderson
came home one night,

15:31.632 --> 15:34.501
twisted on alcohol,
and fell down his basement stairs.

15:34.534 --> 15:38.338
Broken neck. My man's blood-alcohol
level was off the charts.

15:38.740 --> 15:40.708
M.E. ruled it
an accidental death.

15:42.676 --> 15:45.679
- How the widow take it?
- I don't know, I never met her.

15:57.959 --> 16:01.528
- You sleepin' alright, young man?
- Like a baby.

16:02.262 --> 16:05.933
You don't look like it.
For real, Bobby, you okay?

16:05.967 --> 16:09.503
Yeah, the usual shit, the job,
stuff at home. It's nothin' major.

16:09.536 --> 16:13.340
- Don't lie to your daddy.
- I'm fine.

17:04.759 --> 17:08.562
<i>The number you're trying
to reach is no longer in service. Goodbye.</i>

17:35.056 --> 17:38.291
You're sayin' that
Sanderson's hyoid was broke?

17:38.793 --> 17:40.660
According to the report, yes.

17:49.070 --> 17:51.404
He fell down a flight of stairs,
Gwen.

17:51.438 --> 17:53.640
How common
is a hyoid fracture in a fall?

17:53.673 --> 17:58.713
Not very. Strangulation,
hanging, blunt-force trauma,

17:58.746 --> 18:01.481
that breaks the hyoid,
not a fall.

18:01.816 --> 18:03.718
So why was it ruled an accident?

18:03.751 --> 18:09.356
Wasn't my lookout, but, you know,
things do slip through the cracks.

18:09.724 --> 18:12.325
You wanna reanimate
a closed case?

18:12.692 --> 18:14.729
Me? Heh, no.

18:18.099 --> 18:21.803
You owe me for this
and I don't mean coffee.

18:22.837 --> 18:24.437
Dinner.

18:25.438 --> 18:27.340
How about Crisfield's?

18:27.775 --> 18:30.077
I've been dreaming
about their crab imperial.

18:30.111 --> 18:31.678
Now you're trying to spoil me.

18:37.718 --> 18:41.488
What's up with you, Mitch?
You look like your dog died.

18:42.689 --> 18:45.827
I got a conundrum. I don't know
what to do about it.

18:46.493 --> 18:47.929
Care to run it by me?

18:51.398 --> 18:55.803
No. No, it's somethin'
I gotta figure out alone.

18:58.139 --> 18:59.472
Okay.

19:08.381 --> 19:10.918
Alright, okay. Come on, you guys.
Let's find something to watch on TV.

19:10.952 --> 19:14.621
Hold on.
Who knows where the remote is?

19:15.957 --> 19:17.490
I'll help you find it.

19:17.524 --> 19:18.960
Oh, yeah, you will.

19:20.194 --> 19:21.796
Mom!

19:51.591 --> 19:55.462
<i>Hi, you've reached Gina, I'm not
here right now. Please leave a message.</i>

19:56.764 --> 19:58.933
<i>Gina, it's Bobby.
If you're there, pick up.</i>

19:59.934 --> 20:01.869
<i>Can you, um,
can you pick up the phone?</i>

20:01.903 --> 20:04.772
<i>I just need to speak
with you for a second.</i>

20:04.805 --> 20:07.440
<i>Gina, it's Bobby. If you're...
if you're there, pick up.</i>

20:11.846 --> 20:13.981
<i>I need to speak with you, okay?</i>

20:14.982 --> 20:19.186
<i>Just, um...
Please pick up the phone, okay?</i>

20:19.220 --> 20:21.956
<i>Uh, just, just call me back
and, uh...</i>

20:22.689 --> 20:25.793
<i>And I'll talk to you soon, I'll be able
to have my phone all day.</i>

20:37.872 --> 20:40.841
<i>My name is Tonio Harris.</i>

20:41.641 --> 20:44.979
<i>This place where I come up,
it can be kinda rough.</i>

20:46.247 --> 20:50.550
<i>I got problems at home.
Got problems at school.</i>

20:50.952 --> 20:53.988
<i>Hell, I got problems walkin'
down these here streets.</i>

20:55.522 --> 20:59.659
<i>And if you wanna know the truth,
I got problems with my future.</i>

21:05.733 --> 21:07.702
Now, come on.
Now, come on.

21:08.601 --> 21:11.038
- Yeah, yeah.
- Oh, squeeze.

21:11.072 --> 21:14.709
Go for it, Antwan. It was close.
Hey, let me set that, nigga.

21:14.742 --> 21:16.711
- I got it, James bro.
- You don't got him, I got him.

21:16.744 --> 21:17.979
I got him. What's up?

21:20.014 --> 21:21.015
Come on.

21:22.950 --> 21:26.721
Come on, yeah, I got him.
So what's up with you?

21:26.754 --> 21:27.822
Here we go, here we go.

21:27.855 --> 21:30.590
He's about to take you.

21:30.623 --> 21:33.894
- Oh, shit.
- Watch the pick. Watch the pick. Watch it.

21:36.831 --> 21:40.801
- Yay!
- Yay!

21:48.843 --> 21:50.745
Oh, Payless Shoe-wearin' ass,
nigga.

21:52.046 --> 21:53.748
Are we gonna ball or what?

21:55.916 --> 21:57.852
No, we can go instead, though.

22:00.721 --> 22:02.622
Come on, man,
let's run it, y'all.

22:08.661 --> 22:09.930
Hey, slim, I gotta go.

22:11.198 --> 22:14.835
Alright, tell your little sister
that I said, what's up, alright?

22:14.869 --> 22:17.772
Shorty got some nice little titties on
her, you know what I'm sayin'?

22:23.377 --> 22:24.912
Take your ball and go home,
slim.

22:27.748 --> 22:29.150
I see you later, Tonio.

22:29.817 --> 22:31.551
Yo bama ass.

22:35.356 --> 22:38.793
We gonna holler at you
and we gonna see you.

22:52.840 --> 22:56.143
I be seein' that boy around.
He got them nothin' eyes.

22:56.177 --> 22:57.677
Maybe you shouldn't
have schooled him.

22:58.045 --> 23:02.615
Uh, you know, that's just
who I am. This your car?

23:02.649 --> 23:04.819
My father's.
He can't drive no more.

23:06.387 --> 23:07.922
You go to that restaurant
like I told you to?

23:08.823 --> 23:10.124
Yeah, I went.

23:10.858 --> 23:12.860
White boy who interviewed me
was like,

23:12.893 --> 23:14.829
"Do you understand
that the hours are long

23:14.862 --> 23:17.798
and do you think you're gonna
make it to work on time?"

23:17.832 --> 23:20.701
He might as well have gone ahead
and called me a nigger to my face,

23:20.734 --> 23:22.303
'cause then he sat there,

23:22.336 --> 23:25.005
and smiled like he was gonna make a big
announcement or some type of lesson.

23:25.039 --> 23:27.374
Oh, I think,
we'll give you a try.

23:27.408 --> 23:29.977
So I told him, "I don't wanna
work at the joint."

23:30.010 --> 23:32.113
I walked right out of the joint
with my head up high.

23:33.013 --> 23:36.117
You should have taken that job
and showed him he was wrong.

23:36.150 --> 23:39.820
Yo, I can't stand the way white
people be talkin' to me sometimes.

23:39.854 --> 23:42.790
It's like, they only there
to make theyselves feel better.

23:42.823 --> 23:44.925
Like, "Oh, I hired a Negro",
and all that shit.

23:44.959 --> 23:48.395
Well, you gotta do somethin'.
Not tryin' to tell you what to do.

23:48.429 --> 23:50.697
I just don't want you to make
the same mistakes I've made.

23:52.433 --> 23:54.969
Uh, alright, I'mma find a job.

23:56.437 --> 23:59.840
Well, let's get out of here.
I told your mother I see you got home.

23:59.874 --> 24:01.775
Crack that window, too.

24:09.917 --> 24:11.952
<i>My name is Peters.</i>

24:11.986 --> 24:16.157
<i>The younger officers in the Fourth
District call me Sergeant dad.</i>

24:16.190 --> 24:19.093
<i>I don't mind as long as
they say it with respect.</i>

24:20.261 --> 24:24.765
<i>I ride midnights mostly.
I prefer to ride alone.</i>

24:25.065 --> 24:29.970
<i>You get aches and pains when you're
behind the wheel for hours at a stretch.</i>

24:30.938 --> 24:35.109
<i>I should get one of those things
the African cabbies sit on.</i>

24:35.142 --> 24:37.711
<i>Looks like a rack
of wooden balls.</i>

24:38.245 --> 24:41.916
<i>I've been doing this
for 22 years now.</i>

24:41.949 --> 24:48.022
<i>Well, I guess the damage I've done
to my spine or whatever is permanent.</i>

24:49.957 --> 24:54.128
Hey.
Pretty late for her to be out.

24:54.161 --> 24:56.063
It was just hot in my apartment,
we're just getting some air.

24:56.096 --> 25:00.701
Yeah. Been some armed
robberies on this block.

25:01.068 --> 25:02.736
I know,
we won't be out too long.

25:02.770 --> 25:03.804
Okay.

25:19.520 --> 25:22.289
Smile for Officer Friendly.

25:32.866 --> 25:34.301
Where you off to?

25:34.335 --> 25:36.237
Backyard's got a show
at the Hall tonight.

25:36.270 --> 25:38.072
So you weren't even gonna ask me
if you could go?

25:38.872 --> 25:40.074
Do I have to?

25:40.107 --> 25:41.508
as
long you're livin' in my house

25:41.542 --> 25:43.510
and you ain't payin'rent,
yes, you have to.

25:43.544 --> 25:46.146
What you talkin' about,
"Do you have to"?

25:46.180 --> 25:47.281
Can I go?

25:50.251 --> 25:51.318
Yes.

25:52.553 --> 25:55.923
- Just get home early, okay?
- Okay.

25:55.956 --> 25:57.524
Look, you know what, um?

25:57.558 --> 26:00.327
I want you to take that
test again, that college test.

26:01.929 --> 26:03.163
Alright, I will.

26:03.197 --> 26:07.001
They got all types of financial
aid for people like you.

26:07.034 --> 26:09.103
You go to school, talk to one
of those counselors, okay?

26:09.136 --> 26:11.071
Yeah, as soon as I find one.

26:14.208 --> 26:16.877
I put somethin' in the bowl
for you.

26:16.910 --> 26:18.345
Alright, ma, thank you.

26:21.915 --> 26:24.852
So your wife
doesn't wanna press charges.

26:24.885 --> 26:26.287
Don't make no difference to me.

26:26.320 --> 26:29.356
Oh, but you got a
restraining order, Charles.

26:29.390 --> 26:33.927
That's my house, too.
Why can't I visit with my sons?

26:35.596 --> 26:38.365
All due respect, they don't look
too happy to see you.

26:41.101 --> 26:42.870
They'll come around.

26:48.108 --> 26:50.377
I don't wanna see you
again tonight.

26:51.111 --> 26:52.946
The feeling's mutual.

27:00.154 --> 27:06.593
- I miss you at the meetings.
- They say the same shit all the time.

27:06.627 --> 27:10.864
- But it works if you work it.
- That's what I'm talkin' about.

27:20.307 --> 27:21.642
You go ahead now.

27:29.149 --> 27:30.351
Okay.

27:52.139 --> 27:53.273
Hey.

27:55.075 --> 27:56.377
Tonio, right?

27:57.444 --> 28:00.881
- How're you doing tonight?
- Maintainin'.

28:02.216 --> 28:04.017
You going to that concert
over there?

28:05.953 --> 28:06.855
Yeah.

28:06.887 --> 28:09.056
Oh, well,
take care of yourself in there

28:09.089 --> 28:11.425
and tell your mom
Sergeant Peters says hello.

28:23.437 --> 28:26.507
<i>I've been knowin' the
people down here for generations.</i>

28:27.174 --> 28:31.412
<i>Locked up that kid's mother years
ago when she was a teenager.</i>

28:31.445 --> 28:34.681
<i>Darla Harris, that's her name.</i>

